						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine of the Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1559 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1481, Siddhārthin, Āśvija śu. 15, [Sunday].</hi> In Siddhārthin, corresponding to Śaka 1481 there was an intercalary month in Āśvayuja which is not indicated in the record. Taking the month to be Abhika Āśvayuja in which there was a lunar eclipse on the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> specified, the details may be equated with <hi rend="bold">1559 A.D., September 16,</hi> which was, however, a <hi rend="bold">Saturday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Mentions Kallabhāvi and Jaṁgama Vīrayya. The epigraph is very much damaged and the details of the grant are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
